  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Social Media Videographer and Video Editor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><ul><li>Shoot short form content for social media (Instagram Reels, TikTok, XiaoHongShu, YouTube Shorts) using phone and/or camera</li><li>Edit videos end to end: cut, captions, music, sound effects, color correction, simple motion graphics</li><li>Add on screen text, subtitles, hooks, and pacing that fit each platform style</li><li>Repurpose 1 long video into multiple short clips and variations</li><li>Plan shot lists and basic scripts with the content lead, then execute fast</li><li>Manage footage: organize files, name properly, store in cloud, keep backup</li><li>Maintain brand consistency: logo, fonts, colors, intro outro, disclaimer style</li><li>Coordinate filming schedule, locations, and simple lighting or mic setup</li><li>Track performance and suggest improvements based on views, retention, saves, leads</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Media, Film, Communications, or related fields</li><li>Strong editing skills (CapCut, Premiere Pro, Final Cut, DaVinci Resolve is preferred)</li><li>Comfortable filming people, events, and property walkthrough style videos</li><li>Fast turnaround and able to follow a clear style guide</li><li>Good sense of storytelling, hooks, and social media trends</li></ul><p><br />Interested candidates are invited to submit a comprehensive resume, a link to their portfolio, current and expected salary, and date of availability.<br /></p><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted applicants will be notified.</em></p>",
